title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\GkeNodePoolTarget
name: GkeNodePoolTarget
description:
GKE NodePools that Dataproc workloads run on.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.GkeNodePoolTarget

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.roles
params.description: Required. The types of role for a GKE NodePool

params.name: data.node_pool_config
params.description: Optional. The configuration for the GKE NodePool. If specified, Dataproc attempts to create a NodePool with the specified shape. If one with the same name already exists, it is verified against all specified fields. If a field differs, the virtual cluster creation will fail. If omitted, any NodePool with the specified name is used. If a NodePool with the specified name does not exist, Dataproc create a NodePool with default values.
